paojiangdou chau roumou 泡豇豆炒肉末

Longbeans
Ground pork
10 pickled chili peppers
8 dried chili pepper
2 cloves of garlic, sliced
ginger, minced
1 teaspoon Sichuan peppercorns
Soy sauce
1 teaspoon sugar
shaoxing
salt to taste
2 to 4 tablespoons cooking oil

Directions：

Rinse the string bean well.  
Air-dry on a clean rack.
Add the following to a pickling jar
star anise
sichuan peppercorns
1.5L water
240g salt 
40g rock sugar
30g unpeeled garlic
150g sichuan chilies
1 bunch longbeans
30g Baijiu
Wait for about 10 days until they all turn slightly deep yellow color.

In a bowl combine
	150g minced pork
	1tsp soy
	1/4tsp white pepper
	shaoxing

Rinse the longbeans
Dice the longbeans
Slice  the pickled chili peppers too.
Peel and thinly slice the garlic and pickled ginger.  
With a pair of scissors, finely cut the dried chili peppers.

Heat a wok over high heat.  
Add oil, 
garlic slices, 
Sichuan peppercorns, 
ginger, 
dried chili peppers
pickled chili peppers.  
Stir fry for a couple minutes.  
Add ground pork. 
Stir fry until golden brown  
Add shaoxing  
Stir fry for another couple minutes.
Add chopped string beans
add sugar
add salt
add soy
Stir fry over high heat for another 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and serve immediately.  

